com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles

Class CollapsibleNodeStyleDecorator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles.CollapsibleNodeStyleDecorator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    INodeStyle, ICloneable, Cloneable

    public class CollapsibleNodeStyleDecorator
extends Object
implements INodeStyle, Cloneable
    Decorates an arbitrary node styles with an additional collapse/expand handle.

    This style uses the CollapsibleNodeStyleDecoratorRenderer to adorn an existing INodeStyle with a Button that can then be used to trigger the ICommand.TOGGLE_EXPANSION_STATE.

    By default, this handle is rendered as a plus ("+") sign when in collapsed state, and a minus ("-") sign when in expanded state.

    See Also:
    CollapsibleNodeStyleDecoratorRenderer

        public final InsetsD getInsets()

        This effectively influences the way the bounds of a group node are being calculated. The default IGroupBoundsCalculator implementation will use these insets to determine the minimum size of a group node given a set of contained nodes.
